# Data Layer Conventions

## Repository Returns Result<T>
Repositories must catch all exceptions and wrap in `Result`:
```kotlin
override suspend fun getRideDetail(rideId: String): Result<Ride> = runCatching {
    val dto = api.getRideDetail(rideId)
    dto.toDomain()
}
```
Never let a `HttpException` or `IOException` propagate to the domain layer.

## DTO → Domain Mapping
DTOs live in `data/remote/dto/`. Always map to domain models before returning from a repository:
```kotlin
// ✅ GOOD — domain model crosses the layer boundary
fun RideDto.toDomain(): Ride = Ride(id = id, origin = origin, status = Status.from(status))

// ❌ BAD — DTO leaking into domain/UI
fun getRide(): RideDto  // don't do this
```

## Token Refresh Interceptor
The `TokenRefreshInterceptor` handles 401 automatically. Never write token refresh logic in a ViewModel or use case:
```kotlin
// In OkHttp Interceptor — not in ViewModel
if (response.code == 401) {
    val newToken = runBlocking { authRepository.refreshToken() }
    return chain.proceed(request.newBuilder()
        .header("Authorization", "Bearer $newToken").build())
}
```

## DataStore — Typed Preferences Only
```kotlin
// ✅ GOOD — typed keys
val ACCESS_TOKEN = stringPreferencesKey("access_token")
val USER_ROLE    = stringPreferencesKey("user_role")

// ❌ BAD — raw string keys
prefs.edit { putString("access_token", token) }  // SharedPreferences style
```
Sensitive values (access_token, refresh_token) must use **EncryptedDataStore** backed by Android Keystore.

## API Service — suspend functions only
```kotlin
interface RideApiService {
    @GET("rides/{id}")
    suspend fun getRideDetail(@Path("id") rideId: String): RideDto

    @POST("rides")
    suspend fun createRide(@Body request: CreateRideRequest): RideDto
}
```
No RxJava. No callbacks. Coroutines only.
